DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday\, May 27\, from 4–8 PM at Whispering Vine Fourth Street for a Hope Family Wines tasting built around four Paso Robles favorites: Austin Hope Cabernet Sauvignon\, Treana Red Blend\, Quest Red Blend\, and Troublemaker Red Blend.\nTasting Fee: $20 per person\nSpecial Guest: Cam Nicholson\nFeatured Wines:\n- Austin Hope Cabernet Sauvignon 2023 – Winery $62 – Dark ruby and full-bodied\, with black currant\, blackberry\, violet\, mocha\, and dried spice carried by polished tannins and a broad Paso Robles finish.\n- Treana Red Blend 2023 – Winery $39 – A Cabernet Sauvignon and Syrah blend with plum\, black cherry\, violet\, blueberry preserve\, and warm baking spice over firm tannins and a rich finish.\n- Quest Red Blend – Winery $27 – Plush dark fruit\, cocoa\, sweet mint\, and vanilla spice\, finishing with soft tannins and balanced acidity.\n- Troublemaker Red Blend – Winery $20 – Dark cherry\, dried plum\, sage\, black currant\, espresso\, and sweet oak with plush fruit and soft but persistent tannins.\nSpend the evening exploring one of Paso Robles’ most recognizable portfolios with Cam Nicholson and a lineup that moves from polished Cabernet to bold Central Coast blends.
LOCATION:4201 W Fourth St Reno\, NV 89523
SUMMARY:Hope Family Wines Tasting
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR